commit.message: Bump minimal version of python to 3.11

Ensure UTF-8 encoding for all file write operations (#199)

This commit explicitly sets encoding="utf-8" for all instances of path.open("w") across the ChemEx codebase. This change addresses issues related to default system encodings that are not UTF-8, such as cp1251, preventing UnicodeEncodeErrors during file write operations. It enhances the software's compatibility and reliability across different computing environments.

Fixes #196

It enhances the software's compatibility and reliability across different computing environments.

commit.message:
Resolve Pydantic v2 Error with SpinSystem IntegrationResolved an issue where SpinSystem not being a Pydantic model caused errors in dependent Pydantic models. The previous workaround using Annotated and BeforeValidation became ineffective under unclear circumstances. SpinSystem has been converted to a Pydantic model to rectify this.Fixes #195

* Resolve Pydantic v2 Error with SpinSystem Integration

Resolved an issue where SpinSystem not being a Pydantic model caused errors in dependent Pydantic models. The previous workaround using Annotated and BeforeValidation became ineffective under unclear circumstances. SpinSystem has been converted to a Pydantic model to rectify this.

Fixes #195

commit.message: Update Docusaurus
Bump package versions
Update the local optimizer for the algorithm "basinhopping"

Update binding kinetic models with Kd,app

Binding kinetic models with multiple bound states have now an "apparent Kd" that corresponds to the Kd where all the bound states are counted as only one state. It is called "kd_app". The Kd that corresponds to the binding between the free and the "first" bound state is still called "kd_ab" if "a" is free and "b" is the "first" bound state.
Refactoring

commit.message: Bump Docusaurus version

Add an option for per profile error estimation

Add the option "global_error" in the section "[data]" of the experiment
configuration file. When set to "True" the error is estimated using all
the profiles in the dataset. When set to "False" the error is estimated
on a per profile basis. This is defaulted to "True".

Refactorings

commit.message:
New kinetic models, bug fixes and refactoring (#176)

* Fix `path` wrongly converted to lower case (Fix #175)

* Update the calculation of propagators

This is to match the way stacked matrices are dealt with in SciPy. When
there is only one delay to compute, the function
`scipy.linalg.expm` is used instead of the diagonalization approach.

* Use `NonNegativeFloat` instead of `PositiveFloat`

This corrects a bug where `0.0` was not an acceptable value for
`h_larmor_frq`, `p_total`, and `l_total`.

* Add new kinetic models for various oligomerization and binding reactions.

* Bump packages versions to the latest

* Remove pre-commit

* Add docstrings and refactor for code maintenance

* Forbid unknown options in method files

* Refactor "spin_system.py" into a package

* Refactor "pick_cest.py" into a package

* Add 1H EXSY experiment

`scipy.linalg.expm` is used instead of the diagonalization approach.

* Use `NonNegativeFloat` instead of `PositiveFloat`

This corrects a bug where `0.0` was not an acceptable value for
`h_larmor_frq`, `p_total`, and `l_total`.

* Add new kinetic models for various oligomerization and binding reactions.

* Bump packages versions to the latest

* Remove pre-commit

* Add docstrings and refactor for code maintenance

* Forbid unknown options in method files

* Refactor "spin_system.py" into a package

* Refactor "pick_cest.py" into a package

* Add 1H EXSY experiment
